(Moon Chae Won)

5
00:00:29,629 --> 00:00:31,370
(Jang Hee Jin, Seo Hyeon Woo)

6
00:00:33,469 --> 00:00:35,670
(Flower of Evil)

7
00:00:35,670 --> 00:00:38,840
(This program includes
indirect advertisements.)

8
00:01:52,620 --> 00:01:56,489
Should I tell you
what kind of person I am?

9
00:01:59,489 --> 00:02:01,790
I promise to love you a lot
from now.

10
00:02:03,859 --> 00:02:05,459
I'll be good to you.

11
00:02:08,229 --> 00:02:10,740
Then at a certain point,
everything will start to change...

12
00:02:14,469 --> 00:02:15,770
like a lie.

13
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,219
(Where the Morning Star Hovers,
Baek Hee Seong)

14
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,039
What do we do? It's already 4pm!

15
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,409
We don't have time for this.
We're late.

16
00:03:24,439 --> 00:03:26,479
You silly fool.

17
00:03:26,610 --> 00:03:28,610
What if a customer walks in?

18
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:31,150
You're the one who got into the mood
because you liked the music.

19
00:03:31,150 --> 00:03:35,150
Hurry and clean the shop
and get Eun Ha in her best outfit.

20
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:36,650
Make sure the brand name shows.

21
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:39,759
I have to go to the dry cleaner's
to pick up my stuff.

22
00:03:39,759 --> 00:03:42,460
Why are you being so formal
when it's just us?

23
00:03:46,759 --> 00:03:48,930
- What?
- Are you okay with it?

24
00:03:50,669 --> 00:03:53,810
I'm fine with it. I'm just worried
you'd be uncomfortable.

25
00:03:54,169 --> 00:03:57,740
We should see them more often.
They're still your parents.

26
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:01,150
They're Eun Ha's grandparents too.

27
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,949
I'm scared of Grandma.

28
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:06,819
Why are you scared of her?
She's your grandma.

29
00:04:06,990 --> 00:04:08,990
You're scared of her too.

30
00:04:10,689 --> 00:04:12,120
When was I scared of her?

31
00:04:33,949 --> 00:04:36,009
Didn't you teach your daughter
how to greet someone?

32
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:38,319
It's because she remembers you
slamming the door on us...

33
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:39,480
last New Year's Day.

34
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:42,389
It's you who barged in
when I told you not to come.

35
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:45,819
How was your trip here?
Was this place hard to find?

36
00:04:45,819 --> 00:04:46,990
It was okay.

37
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:53,259
Eun Ha. Shall we do
what we practiced earlier?

38
00:04:54,629 --> 00:04:56,170
Come on, try it.

39
00:05:00,670 --> 00:05:04,040
Grandma. Grandpa.

40
00:05:04,779 --> 00:05:06,279
I love you...

41
00:05:16,220 --> 00:05:18,220
Let's go inside. My legs hurt.

42
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:27,730
Grandma hates Eun Ha.

43
00:05:27,730 --> 00:05:29,569
No, it's okay.

44
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,569
If you try 10 times,
it'll work once, at least.

45
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,139
It's okay.

46
00:05:34,769 --> 00:05:38,740
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

47
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:42,110
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

48
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:46,579
- Happy birthday, dear Dad
- Happy birthday, dear honey

49
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:50,089
- Happy birthday to you
- Happy birthday to you

50
00:05:53,459 --> 00:05:54,629
Blow them out.

51
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,629
Eun Ha.

52
00:06:00,629 --> 00:06:02,629
Happy birthday, Dad.

53
00:06:02,629 --> 00:06:05,399
Your present is me. Baek Eun Ha.

54
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:08,139
Really? What a beautiful present.

55
00:06:09,610 --> 00:06:11,709
This is from me.

56
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:14,050
You didn't have to prepare anything.

57
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:23,990
I love it. Thank you.

58
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:25,790
I even engraved your initials on it.

59
00:06:30,829 --> 00:06:31,899
Thank you.

60
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,300
Mom, I have to pee.

61
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:38,399
Okay. Let's go to the washroom.

62
00:06:45,209 --> 00:06:46,980
Did you invite us
so that you could rub it in?

63
00:06:49,610 --> 00:06:51,220
You shouldn't have come.

64
00:06:52,149 --> 00:06:53,620
You could've made up an excuse.

65
00:06:54,089 --> 00:06:56,050
Is it wrong for me to attend
my own son's birthday?

66
00:06:58,389 --> 00:07:01,930
Now, does the life you're leading
seem entirely yours?

67
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,430
Not at all.

68
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:07,100
It has never been mine,
to begin with,

69
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,600
so I don't even know
how it feels to be entirely mine.

70
00:07:10,670 --> 00:07:12,569
Are you being sarcastic with me?

71
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:15,639
If it wasn't for me...

72
00:07:20,379 --> 00:07:21,480
That's enough.

73
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:25,079
We're all in the same boat.

74
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:29,389
If you don't want it to sink,
don't provoke each other.

75
00:07:36,129 --> 00:07:37,329
- Sit down.
- Okay.

76
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:40,329
Hee Seong, I...

77
00:07:40,870 --> 00:07:42,670
Okay. Should I drop you off?

78
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:44,870
No, it's okay. I can take a cab.

79
00:07:46,339 --> 00:07:48,740
Mother and Father, I'm sorry.

80
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:50,009
Something came up.

81
00:07:50,139 --> 00:07:52,379
You're taking revenge because
I slammed the door in your face...

82
00:07:52,709 --> 00:07:54,050
last year, right?

83
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:55,579
It's not like that.

84
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:59,680
I really wanted
to treat you to a meal today.

85
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,589
It's cold outside. Wear this.

86
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:02,850
It's okay.

87
00:08:03,220 --> 00:08:05,290
What should I do? I got
on the wrong side of her again.

88
00:08:05,990 --> 00:08:07,089
It's fine.

89
00:08:08,759 --> 00:08:10,029
I'll be going, then.

90
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:32,279
She must be stupider than I thought.

91
00:08:34,149 --> 00:08:35,350
Your wife, that is.

92
00:08:36,019 --> 00:08:37,389
We didn't know...

93
00:08:37,860 --> 00:08:40,519
your marriage life
would be this happy.

94
00:08:43,659 --> 00:08:45,299
It's because we're soulmates.

95
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:47,629
Ji Won and I.

96
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:49,669
What?

97
00:08:51,169 --> 00:08:54,539
(Gangsu Police Station)

98
00:09:02,110 --> 00:09:05,850
Someone who has a dirty past
like you are soulmates...

99
00:09:06,179 --> 00:09:07,620
with a cop?

100
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,659
You know how to be funny.

101
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:24,799
You've become more human.

102
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,370
Be honest.

103
00:09:29,669 --> 00:09:31,909
This is still very important to us.

104
00:09:34,149 --> 00:09:35,649
Now that you have a child,

105
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:40,620
have you become fond of her?

106
00:09:43,590 --> 00:09:46,590
Ji Won only believes things
that she sees.

107
00:09:48,429 --> 00:09:52,230
And I only show her the things
I want her to see.

108
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,200
She's...

109
00:09:55,330 --> 00:09:57,029
very simple.

110
00:09:59,039 --> 00:10:00,139
So...

111
00:10:02,710 --> 00:10:04,440
you don't have to worry.

112
00:10:36,710 --> 00:10:40,179
At an apartment in Seokin-dong
at 3pm today,

113
00:10:41,049 --> 00:10:43,179
a boy was found unconscious
on the staircase.

114
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:45,649
His head was severely injured.

115
00:10:46,620 --> 00:10:49,120
His name is Kim In Seo,
and he is 12.

116
00:10:51,019 --> 00:10:53,159
- In Seo.
- In Seo.

117
00:10:54,330 --> 00:10:55,460
Are you okay?

118
00:10:56,659 --> 00:10:59,159
After undergoing surgery,
he didn't speak for some time.

119
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:00,500
Then the first thing he said was...

120
00:11:06,740 --> 00:11:07,870
It was him.

121
00:11:09,409 --> 00:11:11,309
Dad did it.

122
00:11:13,179 --> 00:11:15,409
He tried to kill me.

123
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:21,549
"It was him. Dad did it."

124
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,460
According to his testimony...

125
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:47,039
Go back down.

126
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:50,480
Dad, I'm very exhausted.

127
00:11:50,879 --> 00:11:52,350
I want to stop.

128
00:11:52,450 --> 00:11:54,190
- Go.
- I'm too tired.

129
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:01,389
Look at your stomach.

130
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,259
Aren't you disgusted with yourself?

131
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,129
I'm... I'm sorry.

132
00:12:06,830 --> 00:12:08,629
- Kim In Seo.
- Yes?

133
00:12:15,039 --> 00:12:17,610
Every time I look at you,
I become enraged.

134
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:20,379
I can't believe you're my son.

135
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:51,240
He's lying, he's lying.

136
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:54,080
My son is lying.

137
00:12:55,549 --> 00:12:57,080
Mr. Kim Sang Jin.

138
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:59,450
Are you claiming...

139
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:00,750
that your 12-year-old son
is lying...

140
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:04,860
so that he can put you behind bars
for attempted murder?

141
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:07,120
"Attempted murder"?

142
00:13:08,929 --> 00:13:12,059
A child was severely injured
on a steep staircase...

143
00:13:12,059 --> 00:13:13,700
with no cameras around.

144
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:16,029
His dad who was with him
suddenly disappeared,

145
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:18,600
and the boy claimed
that his dad did it.

146
00:13:20,139 --> 00:13:23,409
You do know that it's reasonable
for us to be suspicious,

147
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:25,110
don't you?

148
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:26,409
Come on, you can do it.

149
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:28,279
It's true that I made him
walk up the stairs.

150
00:13:28,279 --> 00:13:29,279
Good boy.

151
00:13:29,279 --> 00:13:31,049
But what he said was not true.

152
00:13:31,049 --> 00:13:33,720
You can do it, my son.
Hang in there.

153
00:13:34,289 --> 00:13:35,519
Good.

154
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,389
Hey, Eun Seok.

155
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:45,730
Right now? Okay, I'll be there.

156
00:13:46,929 --> 00:13:48,230
You should go home first.

157
00:13:48,399 --> 00:13:49,799
I'll go home in the evening.

158
00:13:50,399 --> 00:13:51,539
Make sure to stretch.

159
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:56,440
That's all.

160
00:13:58,279 --> 00:14:02,379
My friend called and said
he was nearby, so we had a drink.

161
00:14:03,049 --> 00:14:04,850
That's when my wife called.

162
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:07,850
Detective.

163
00:14:09,389 --> 00:14:10,850
How could a parent do such a thing?

164
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:14,759
He's my precious boy.

165
00:14:18,159 --> 00:14:19,259
This is horrible.

166
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,330
It just doesn't make sense.

167
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:30,039
What are you doing?

168
00:14:30,039 --> 00:14:31,679
You had ribs, soju, and beer...

169
00:14:32,409 --> 00:14:33,980
with your friend?

170
00:14:38,179 --> 00:14:39,250
Yes.

171
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,809
Do you think he really did
that horrendous deed to his own son?

172
00:15:03,309 --> 00:15:06,039
He looks like a very decent guy
on the outside.

173
00:15:06,509 --> 00:15:09,710
Over 80 percent of those
guilty of child abuse are parents.

174
00:15:10,450 --> 00:15:13,120
Ji Won, what's your take on this?

175
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:16,649
He seems to be falsely accused.

176
00:15:16,820 --> 00:15:19,220
Every single person
we've interrogated seemed that way.

177
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:20,519
Come on, you're better than this.

178
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:22,629
No, look at his shoes.

179
00:15:22,759 --> 00:15:25,029
His shoes? What about them?

180
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:28,429
Judging by his clothes,
I don't think they're his.

181
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:30,129
They're the restaurant's slippers.

182
00:15:31,269 --> 00:15:34,970
While eating, he heard that his son
was injured and hurried out.

183
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:37,570
And only one of his socks is dirty.

184
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:44,179
The slipper probably fell off
since it wasn't his size.

185
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:48,889
Judging by the circumstances,
isn't this proof that he's innocent?

186
00:15:50,289 --> 00:15:51,360
I knew it.

187
00:15:51,919 --> 00:15:54,529
That's your problem.

188
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:57,090
- What is?
- You have blind faith in evidence.

189
00:15:57,090 --> 00:15:59,429
You should put his character
before evidence.

190
00:15:59,529 --> 00:16:00,759
You didn't notice...

191
00:16:00,759 --> 00:16:02,029
- his slippers, right?
- Be quiet.

192
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:06,769
Then do you really believe
that he tried to kill his own son?

193
00:16:07,539 --> 00:16:08,610
Hear me out.

194
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:11,179
After I entered that room,

195
00:16:11,639 --> 00:16:14,080
he and I locked eyes.

196
00:16:16,879 --> 00:16:18,250
And I sensed it!

197
00:16:19,379 --> 00:16:21,990
I sensed that he was the culprit.

198
00:16:21,990 --> 00:16:23,519
Hey, check out these goosebumps.

199
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:24,990
You know what this means.

200
00:16:24,990 --> 00:16:26,720
- You know it, right?
- Of course.

201
00:16:26,789 --> 00:16:29,090
- Ho Joon, what's your take on this?
- Me?

202
00:16:29,259 --> 00:16:30,960
Is it me or Ji Won? Hurry up.

203
00:16:32,059 --> 00:16:34,129
I wasn't going to say this,

204
00:16:34,129 --> 00:16:36,870
but he told me
that I was his role model.

205
00:16:38,070 --> 00:16:41,269
Hey, Im Ho Joon.
You said I was your role model.

206
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:42,539
What?

207
00:16:44,379 --> 00:16:45,909
No, I meant...

208
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:49,049
both of you are my role models.

209
00:16:49,049 --> 00:16:51,549
She and I are totally different.

210
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:54,250
We've been summoned.

211
00:16:54,419 --> 00:16:56,149
Where are you going?
I'm talking to you.

212
00:17:04,329 --> 00:17:07,529
I don't know if
you're aware of this,

213
00:17:07,869 --> 00:17:10,130
but when you buy coffee,
they pack it up nice and neatly...

214
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:11,400
if you buy some extra cups.

215
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,640
I know.

216
00:17:12,769 --> 00:17:13,900
So you knew.

217
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,809
He knew, yet he only bought
coffee for himself?

218
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:20,009
- Detective Cha.
- Yes?

219
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:23,279
Question people around Kim Sang Jin.

220
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:26,450
And check the security footage
near the crime scene as well.

221
00:17:26,819 --> 00:17:28,019
Yes, sir.

222
00:17:28,549 --> 00:17:30,690
Detective Choi,
check Kim Sang Jin's...

223
00:17:30,690 --> 00:17:34,630
I'll beat Kim Sang Jin up
and make him tell us the truth.

224
00:17:35,029 --> 00:17:37,130
Check where he was
when the incident occurred.

225
00:17:37,230 --> 00:17:39,299
And remember to use
legal measures only.

226
00:17:42,529 --> 00:17:44,900
You can trust me, Captain.

227
00:17:45,869 --> 00:17:49,039
We'll go meet
Kim Sang Jin's wife first.

228
00:17:51,539 --> 00:17:52,579
What?

229
00:17:53,539 --> 00:17:55,480
I don't understand what you mean.

230
00:17:56,349 --> 00:17:58,319
I'm sorry, sir.

231
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:01,549
Can you tell me one more time?

232
00:18:01,549 --> 00:18:04,960
Did your husband usually show
an oppressive...

233
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:08,490
or authoritative attitude
towards your son?

234
00:18:08,829 --> 00:18:10,630
He tends to have a firm attitude.

235
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:12,400
My husband...

236
00:18:12,630 --> 00:18:15,470
doesn't like it
when his plan is altered.

237
00:18:15,470 --> 00:18:18,269
He has a fixation for his plans.

238
00:18:19,099 --> 00:18:22,609
Have you ever felt he lacks
a sense of empathy?

239
00:18:23,470 --> 00:18:25,910
What? What do you mean?

240
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:29,380
Are you already thinking of
a headline, Mr. Kim?

241
00:18:31,980 --> 00:18:33,119
(I Hate My Obese Child)

242
00:18:33,119 --> 00:18:34,650
"I Hate My Obese Child".

243
00:18:34,789 --> 00:18:36,650
"The dad that made his son
climb the stairs of death."

244
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:37,650
What do you think?

245
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:40,690
Mr. Kim, do you know
you look overly excited right now?

246
00:18:41,019 --> 00:18:42,930
You should hold back,
since we're in a hospital.

247
00:18:43,289 --> 00:18:46,230
To be honest, this is totally
my type of case.

248
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:51,400
Well, I found the articles you post
on the internet lately pretty fun.

249
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:52,599
Which one did you like the most?

250
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:56,769
That one, the serial murder case
in Yeonju.

251
00:18:57,210 --> 00:18:59,910
I never knew there was a case
like that in our country.

252
00:19:01,039 --> 00:19:04,079
It was awful.
The whole neighborhood was...

253
00:19:04,819 --> 00:19:05,920
What?

254
00:19:06,150 --> 00:19:09,319
Never mind. What's the father's job?

255
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:11,460
- Who?
- The stairs of death.

256
00:19:12,559 --> 00:19:14,930
- He's an attorney.
- An elite father?

257
00:19:16,089 --> 00:19:19,059
This is really nice. It's perfect.

258
00:19:20,029 --> 00:19:22,200
I even like how my pen
doesn't work right now.

259
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,900
Sir, use this.

260
00:19:24,539 --> 00:19:25,539
What is this?

261
00:19:25,569 --> 00:19:27,910
Detective Cha's husband
