Do you two know each other?

523
00:37:31,190 --> 00:37:33,519
- What?
- Do you know...

524
00:37:34,190 --> 00:37:35,320
Detective Cha?

525
00:37:36,829 --> 00:37:39,559
Yes, a bit.

526
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:48,769
Do you want some tea?

527
00:37:49,670 --> 00:37:50,710
What?

528
00:37:51,170 --> 00:37:52,739
I happen to have some nice tea.

529
00:38:06,920 --> 00:38:09,030
Why couldn't you tell Ms. Go
back there?

530
00:38:09,889 --> 00:38:11,360
You pitied her, didn't you?

531
00:38:12,699 --> 00:38:14,329
It's not that.

532
00:38:15,699 --> 00:38:18,329
I knew Detective Choi didn't pick
that phone up by coincidence.

533
00:38:18,530 --> 00:38:21,070
I didn't tell her because
it wasn't valid proof.

534
00:38:22,139 --> 00:38:23,840
Had she known he had cheated on her,

535
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:25,980
she could've shared
some crucial information.

536
00:38:25,980 --> 00:38:27,539
Think sensibly.

537
00:38:27,809 --> 00:38:30,550
His affair and this case
have no connections.

538
00:38:36,619 --> 00:38:38,789
Recently, Kim Sang Jin asked
a fellow lawyer for some advice...

539
00:38:38,789 --> 00:38:40,659
regarding divorce and child support.

540
00:38:40,820 --> 00:38:43,329
He seemed very reluctant
about paying child support.

541
00:38:44,489 --> 00:38:45,929
Are you still wasting your time?

542
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:49,869
I hear Kim Sang Jin and his son
regularly went hiking together.

543
00:38:50,070 --> 00:38:52,329
It was for the past seven years,
and they were happy about it.

544
00:38:53,340 --> 00:38:57,070
Do you know what kind of lunatics
cause the biggest headache?

545
00:38:59,539 --> 00:39:01,280
One who's very patient.

546
00:39:07,719 --> 00:39:11,050
My gosh, Hyun Su.

547
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:14,360
Thanks.

548
00:39:15,460 --> 00:39:16,889
I barely recognized you.

549
00:39:17,260 --> 00:39:18,389
But you did.

550
00:39:21,159 --> 00:39:23,699
Right. That's because...

551
00:39:23,699 --> 00:39:26,269
you and I grew up
in the same neighborhood.

552
00:39:26,570 --> 00:39:28,039
Anyway, you've changed a lot.

553
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:35,210
Don't you think
it's a bit hot today?

554
00:39:36,179 --> 00:39:37,349
I'm sweating.

555
00:39:37,579 --> 00:39:38,679
Is that so?

556
00:39:41,550 --> 00:39:42,949
I feel fine.

557
00:39:47,489 --> 00:39:48,590
Is it just me?

558
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:53,860
Your body temperature keeps rising
because you're holding back.

559
00:39:54,260 --> 00:39:56,570
- What?
- You can ask me.

560
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,800
Ask me the question
that popped into your head...

561
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:00,840
the moment you saw me.

562
00:40:05,639 --> 00:40:08,210
There is none. Don't be absurd.

563
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:10,480
My goodness. There's none.

564
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:18,150
I should go now.
I have an appointment.

565
00:40:18,650 --> 00:40:19,860
Don't you want to know?

566
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:23,730
I bet you're curious.

567
00:40:26,199 --> 00:40:27,329
Aren't you a reporter?

568
00:40:31,869 --> 00:40:33,099
Ask me.

569
00:40:46,250 --> 00:40:48,050
First of all,

570
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:50,389
I don't believe anything
until proven otherwise.

571
00:40:51,650 --> 00:40:53,719
The rumors about you...

572
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,829
are still fictitious to me.

573
00:41:02,699 --> 00:41:03,800
Really?

574
00:41:06,869 --> 00:41:10,440
Hyun Su, I don't know
if you know this.

575
00:41:11,610 --> 00:41:13,179
But 18 years ago,

576
00:41:15,110 --> 00:41:17,309
on the day you disappeared,

577
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:21,119
there was a murder.

578
00:41:24,250 --> 00:41:25,550
Our village head...

579
00:41:27,489 --> 00:41:28,659
was killed.

580
00:41:44,539 --> 00:41:45,710
So?

581
00:41:51,250 --> 00:41:52,550
Do you have anything...

582
00:41:54,119 --> 00:41:55,280
to do with it?

583
00:42:13,900 --> 00:42:17,010
Yesterday, Ddol ran away.

584
00:42:20,309 --> 00:42:22,280
Ddol! Come here!

585
00:42:22,809 --> 00:42:24,050
Ddol!

586
00:42:30,949 --> 00:42:34,820
Ddol had bitten In Seo before,

587
00:42:35,960 --> 00:42:39,260
so he's scared of Ddol.

588
00:42:44,230 --> 00:42:46,570
You should've told me about this.

589
00:42:47,239 --> 00:42:51,269
His mom said she'd euthanize Ddol...

590
00:42:51,670 --> 00:42:54,079
if it happened again.

591
00:42:55,010 --> 00:42:56,750
That's why I couldn't tell you.

592
00:42:58,079 --> 00:43:01,920
In Seo's mom is very strict
and thorough.

593
00:43:03,019 --> 00:43:06,059
She must've intimidated my son.

594
00:43:10,530 --> 00:43:12,489
What? "Ddol"?

595
00:43:14,130 --> 00:43:17,869
Are you telling me
that the culprit was a dog?

596
00:43:17,869 --> 00:43:19,539
Aren't you relieved...

597
00:43:19,639 --> 00:43:21,500
that it's not his dad?

598
00:43:23,269 --> 00:43:27,179
The boy accurately remembered
what In Seo wore that day.

599
00:43:27,679 --> 00:43:30,409
His testimony was detailed.
It's highly credible.

600
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:33,579
Then why in the world...

601
00:43:33,579 --> 00:43:36,119
did In Seo accuse his own dad?

602
00:43:36,519 --> 00:43:38,150
Based on what the others told me,

603
00:43:38,150 --> 00:43:40,119
he was extremely stressed
about losing weight.

604
00:43:40,619 --> 00:43:42,260
Shouldn't we hand this over
to the Women and Juvenile Division?

605
00:43:43,630 --> 00:43:45,059
I'm sure I sensed it.

606
00:43:45,590 --> 00:43:49,469
Jae Seop, can I tell you
a favorite saying of mine?

607
00:43:49,699 --> 00:43:50,869
No.

608
00:43:51,400 --> 00:43:53,699
"An investigation based on
an incorrect assumption..."

609
00:43:53,869 --> 00:43:57,170
- "is wasting your time."
- "is wasting your time."

610
00:43:59,780 --> 00:44:00,980
Darn it.

611
00:44:03,550 --> 00:44:04,650
What's wrong?

612
00:44:04,650 --> 00:44:06,349
It's my wisdom tooth.

613
00:44:13,860 --> 00:44:16,159
You're allowed to go home.

614
00:44:17,659 --> 00:44:18,989
We found a witness.

615
00:44:28,969 --> 00:44:31,010
What's the point in denying?

616
00:44:33,139 --> 00:44:36,010
Everyone thinks that I did it.

617
00:44:36,679 --> 00:44:38,949
You, the village people,

618
00:44:39,719 --> 00:44:40,849
and even the police.

619
00:44:42,750 --> 00:44:45,349
Why did they find the murder weapon
in your backpack?

620
00:44:47,090 --> 00:44:48,489
Why are you still wanted?

621
00:44:49,260 --> 00:44:50,590
If you're innocent,

622
00:44:50,590 --> 00:44:52,389
you should be interrogated
voluntarily...

623
00:44:52,630 --> 00:44:53,900
and clear your name.

624
00:45:00,670 --> 00:45:02,869
How did you know
that I'm still wanted?

625
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:05,039
Did you look into it?

626
00:45:05,940 --> 00:45:07,079
Why?

627
00:45:09,079 --> 00:45:10,349
Well...

628
00:45:11,409 --> 00:45:13,579
I just heard it from somewhere.

629
00:45:13,579 --> 00:45:15,780
When you're a reporter...

630
00:45:17,019 --> 00:45:19,619
I should really go now.
Thanks for the tea.

631
00:45:19,920 --> 00:45:20,989
What now?

632
00:45:22,420 --> 00:45:24,360
Are you going to scurry
over to the police station...

633
00:45:24,730 --> 00:45:26,059
and say that you met Do Hyun Su,

634
00:45:26,059 --> 00:45:27,829
the murderer who killed
the village head in Gagyeong-ri...

635
00:45:27,829 --> 00:45:29,260
18 years ago?

636
00:45:31,599 --> 00:45:32,670
Is that what you're going to do?

637
00:45:34,340 --> 00:45:35,900
Come on.

638
00:45:36,510 --> 00:45:38,710
I'm not that interested
in other people's business.

639
00:45:46,079 --> 00:45:48,920
How about we talk about you
instead of me?

640
00:45:49,789 --> 00:45:50,889
Well, I'm...

641
00:45:52,320 --> 00:45:53,420
Are you married?

642
00:45:56,630 --> 00:45:58,429
Eating and drinking alone
is the trend lately.

643
00:45:58,690 --> 00:45:59,829
And I'm a trendy guy.

644
00:46:00,699 --> 00:46:01,829
I better get going.

645
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:04,230
Did you say you're a reporter
for a weekly magazine?

646
00:46:04,900 --> 00:46:06,400
It's nothing much.

647
00:46:06,969 --> 00:46:09,469
- I'll see you then.
- Then...

648
00:46:12,409 --> 00:46:14,079
I guess you have flexible
working hours.

649
00:46:27,090 --> 00:46:28,559
Which one doesn't have side effects?

650
00:46:28,820 --> 00:46:30,090
There's no medicine like that.

651
00:46:30,090 --> 00:46:31,559
Even vitamins have side effects.

652
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:34,929
It's three dollars.

653
00:46:35,730 --> 00:46:37,030
(Multivitamins)

654
00:46:37,030 --> 00:46:38,269
Let me see.

655
00:46:38,900 --> 00:46:40,039
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

656
00:46:41,269 --> 00:46:42,909
- Ji Won, let's go.
- Okay.

657
00:46:45,539 --> 00:46:47,079
You should just pluck
that tooth out.

658
00:46:47,079 --> 00:46:49,010
How could I just pluck out
a healthy tooth?

659
00:46:49,179 --> 00:46:50,780
It's mine even if it hurts.
I'll never get rid of it.

660
00:46:53,449 --> 00:46:54,550
What is it?

661
00:46:57,690 --> 00:46:58,750
What's wrong?

662
00:47:00,119 --> 00:47:02,590
These are the vitamins Ms. Go takes.

663
00:47:03,130 --> 00:47:04,489
Yes. So?

664
00:47:04,630 --> 00:47:07,300
Do you remember the color of
the pills she spilled?

665
00:47:10,170 --> 00:47:11,230
They were white.

666
00:47:24,210 --> 00:47:26,079
There's nothing wrong
with our family.

667
00:47:26,150 --> 00:47:27,920
There's been nothing wrong
all this time!

668
00:47:33,389 --> 00:47:36,929
In Seo's mom is very strict
and thorough.

669
00:47:37,460 --> 00:47:38,559
His name is...

670
00:47:42,329 --> 00:47:43,570
What was it again?

671
00:47:43,769 --> 00:47:45,369
Why can't I recall?

672
00:47:54,110 --> 00:47:55,340
Can you step out for a second?

673
00:47:55,980 --> 00:47:58,349
Why? I want to stay.

674
00:47:58,449 --> 00:47:59,550
Please.

675
00:48:01,949 --> 00:48:03,090
Okay.

676
00:48:13,300 --> 00:48:15,900
Is there anything left
to investigate?

677
00:48:16,929 --> 00:48:17,929
(Record)

678
00:48:21,570 --> 00:48:22,670
It's you, isn't it?

679
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:25,309
The one who put the cockroach
in the bottle.

680
00:48:26,539 --> 00:48:28,639
To stop your mom from taking them.

681
00:48:33,619 --> 00:48:37,190
I know there's a reason
why you lied.

682
00:48:42,090 --> 00:48:45,030
In Seo, let's have your mom...

683
00:48:46,260 --> 00:48:48,530
make the choice on her own.

684
00:48:54,500 --> 00:48:55,639
I want my mom...

685
00:48:57,539 --> 00:48:58,639
Yes?

686
00:48:59,639 --> 00:49:01,340
to leave.

687
00:49:15,659 --> 00:49:19,289
I don't want her to hear what I say.

688
00:49:23,329 --> 00:49:24,900
- Dad is...
- There you go.

689
00:49:24,900 --> 00:49:26,099
a good person.

690
00:49:26,969 --> 00:49:28,139
To me, at least.

691
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:30,139
In Seo!

692
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:32,610
Hello.

693
00:49:33,239 --> 00:49:35,139
- You're here.
- How have you been?

694
00:49:38,150 --> 00:49:39,349
Dad, can I have some tissue?

695
00:49:39,449 --> 00:49:40,519
Take the picture.

696
00:49:44,590 --> 00:49:46,420
- Did you bring it?
- Yes.

697
00:49:49,489 --> 00:49:50,730
It's not too dangerous, is it?

698
00:49:51,190 --> 00:49:53,659
It's a drug that will block
her neural stimulation temporarily.

699
00:49:53,860 --> 00:49:55,500
Once she stops taking it,
she'll be fine.

700
00:49:56,630 --> 00:49:58,199
She's become
a totally different person.

701
00:49:59,000 --> 00:50:02,170
She's slow, sluggish,
and blank all day.

702
00:50:03,139 --> 00:50:04,309
One time...

703
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:06,980
Honey.

704
00:50:08,239 --> 00:50:09,309
What is this?

705
00:50:10,679 --> 00:50:11,980
It seems like lipstick.

706
00:50:12,349 --> 00:50:13,719
She saw that smudge.

707
00:50:14,380 --> 00:50:16,179
So I just blurted out...

708
00:50:17,050 --> 00:50:18,119
It's paint.

709
00:50:18,949 --> 00:50:20,090
Paint?

710
00:50:20,090 --> 00:50:22,789
I went to a cafe that had just
gone through a renovation.

711
00:50:23,360 --> 00:50:24,489
I guess it got on my shirt.

712
00:50:32,730 --> 00:50:35,340
You're right. It looks like paint.

713
00:50:38,539 --> 00:50:39,880
What's wrong with me lately?

714
00:50:42,179 --> 00:50:44,309
Just make sure she signs
the papers now.

715
00:50:45,150 --> 00:50:46,780
Why is getting divorced
so difficult?

716
00:50:46,949 --> 00:50:48,420
Then did you think
it would be easy...

717
00:50:49,789 --> 00:50:52,989
to get custody and all the money
when you're cheating?

718
00:50:54,360 --> 00:50:55,489
Cut it out.

719
00:50:57,360 --> 00:50:59,489
I couldn't tell my mom.

720
00:51:01,329 --> 00:51:03,800
I told myself I should tell her
numerously...

721
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:05,400
(Recording)

722
00:51:05,400 --> 00:51:06,900
but I couldn't say it.

723
00:51:08,800 --> 00:51:10,039
So I thought...

724
00:51:12,070 --> 00:51:13,710
if my dad was mean to me,

725
00:51:15,309 --> 00:51:16,409
then...

726
00:51:17,210 --> 00:51:20,150
my mom wouldn't be so sad.

727
00:51:21,849 --> 00:51:22,949
I'm sorry.

728
00:51:35,900 --> 00:51:37,929
What are they talking about?

729
00:51:38,869 --> 00:51:40,940
You're forcing a minor to make
a statement...

730
00:51:41,500 --> 00:51:43,969
without a parent next to him.

731
00:51:46,070 --> 00:51:47,639
I'll never let this slide.

732
00:52:00,920 --> 00:52:02,360
Did you get the answer you wanted...

733
00:52:03,460 --> 00:52:05,429
about child abuse
or whatever nonsense?

734
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:08,699
You should know well
since you're an attorney.

735
00:52:09,199 --> 00:52:10,500
What kind of crime it is...

736
00:52:10,500 --> 00:52:13,500
to make someone take drugs secretly
without their consent.

737
00:52:14,670 --> 00:52:15,840
Mr. Kim Sang Jin.

738
00:52:16,170 --> 00:52:19,170
You're under arrest for causing
bodily damage to Ms. Go Hae Yeong.

739
00:52:19,840 --> 00:52:22,139
You have the right
to remain silent...

740
00:52:22,340 --> 00:52:24,480
and the right to an attorney.

741
00:52:42,800 --> 00:52:44,369
Hey, there's no need for that.

742
00:52:44,530 --> 00:52:46,539
I don't need a gift. It's okay.

743
00:52:47,940 --> 00:52:49,769
I'm asking you not to tell anyone
you saw me here.

744
00:52:50,670 --> 00:52:51,739
It's a bribe.

745
00:52:52,610 --> 00:52:54,309
Hey, I'm good at keeping secrets.

746
00:52:55,280 --> 00:52:56,510
Don't worry about it.

747
00:52:59,349 --> 00:53:02,650
Mu Jin, can you come over here
and write your address?

748
00:53:03,050 --> 00:53:04,320
I'll send it to your home.

749
00:53:09,260 --> 00:53:10,360
Okay.

750
00:53:23,369 --> 00:53:24,840
I don't see Mr. Baek Hee Seong.

751
00:53:26,539 --> 00:53:28,139
I heard he owns this place.

752
00:53:28,139 --> 00:53:29,579
(Where the Morning Star Hovers)

753
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:56,809
Do you think she really didn't know?

754
00:53:56,909 --> 00:53:58,739
What? What are you talking about?

755
00:53:59,510 --> 00:54:00,739
I mean Ms. Go.

756
00:54:01,780 --> 00:54:04,550
Do you really think she didn't know
what Kim Sang Jin was doing?

757
00:54:04,550 --> 00:54:06,510
Come on, if she knew that,

758
00:54:06,510 --> 00:54:09,449
would she have taken the drugs
he gave her?

759
00:54:13,019 --> 00:54:14,519
Something crossed my mind though.

760
00:54:14,619 --> 00:54:16,960
(Multivitamins)

761
00:54:22,400 --> 00:54:25,730
If a certain truth can destroy
your life instantly,

762
00:54:27,340 --> 00:54:29,599
and you also know that the truth...

763
00:54:29,869 --> 00:54:32,139
will be revealed someday.

764
00:54:33,070 --> 00:54:35,679
But if you can put off
that moment for another day,

765
00:54:38,980 --> 00:54:40,449
I would take that pill.

766
00:54:40,719 --> 00:54:43,050
What? Have you lost your mind?

767
00:54:43,320 --> 00:54:44,349
Me too.

768
00:54:44,789 --> 00:54:47,420
I just eat anything
my wife gives me.

769
00:54:47,619 --> 00:54:50,489
And one day, if my wife
puts poison into my mouth,

770
00:54:50,489 --> 00:54:53,730
I'd rather die than taking it out
and checking what it is.

771
00:54:54,829 --> 00:54:56,260
What's wrong with you
married people?

772
00:54:56,400 --> 00:54:57,630
I don't want to get married
even more.

773
00:54:57,869 --> 00:54:59,699
I was right eventually.

774
00:55:00,969 --> 00:55:02,070
What do you mean?

775
00:55:02,500 --> 00:55:05,039
I was right.
Kim Sang Jin was the bad guy.

776
00:55:05,269 --> 00:55:08,840
No, it's not like Kim Sang Jin
hurt In Seo.

777
00:55:09,239 --> 00:55:10,480
Stop being stubborn.

778
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:12,679
You're such a bad judge
of character.

779
00:55:13,349 --> 00:55:14,719
Ho Joon, you tell us.

780
00:55:14,949 --> 00:55:17,050
Me? Tell you what?

781
00:55:17,150 --> 00:55:19,289
Who's right? Me or Ji Won?

782
00:55:21,019 --> 00:55:22,960
Well, I think both of you...

783
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:24,260
Just choose one of us.

784
00:55:24,260 --> 00:55:25,960
Don't try anything funny.

785
00:55:26,289 --> 00:55:27,329
I think...

786
00:55:28,599 --> 00:55:30,769
Someone's calling you, Ji Won.
Your phone.

787
00:55:30,769 --> 00:55:31,829
(Mother)

788
00:55:33,599 --> 00:55:34,639
Right.

789
00:55:35,070 --> 00:55:37,269
Tell me. Sit back down.

790
00:55:40,480 --> 00:55:41,539
Yes, Mother.

791
00:55:41,880 --> 00:55:43,039
I don't like you.

792
00:55:44,949 --> 00:55:47,519
- Sorry?
- Are you in your right mind?

793
00:55:48,150 --> 00:55:50,190
Do you think you're good enough
for Hee Seong?

794
00:55:50,619 --> 00:55:52,750
He's the son of the director
of a hospital.

795
00:55:54,289 --> 00:55:56,090
I'll try harder, Mother.

796
00:55:56,559 --> 00:55:58,559
I heard daughters take after
their moms.

797
00:55:59,090 --> 00:56:00,929
Your mom tormented her husband.

798
00:56:05,730 --> 00:56:06,969
Mother, that's a bit harsh...

799
00:56:06,969 --> 00:56:09,139
You haven't changed a bit, have you?

800
00:56:09,900 --> 00:56:12,110
You got yourself pregnant
and married my son,

801
00:56:12,369 --> 00:56:14,440
and now you use your daughter
as an excuse?

802
00:56:14,780 --> 00:56:16,980
Do you think I'll give you
any of my money?

803
00:56:19,909 --> 00:56:22,519
Listen carefully. You disgust me.

804
00:56:23,789 --> 00:56:26,389
Let's pretend we're strangers
to each other.

805
00:56:26,650 --> 00:56:27,860
Don't forget that.

806
00:56:29,889 --> 00:56:32,730
- Mother
- What? Do you feel angry?

807
00:56:36,130 --> 00:56:37,300
It's not that.

808
00:56:38,130 --> 00:56:39,329
About what you said today.

809
00:56:40,800 --> 00:56:42,800
I hope Hee Seong
doesn't know about it.

810
00:56:45,539 --> 00:56:48,210
Although he doesn't say anything,
he's very stressed...

811
00:56:49,780 --> 00:56:51,309
to see you and me in conflict.

812
00:58:17,469 --> 00:58:18,630
- It's pretty.
- Is it?

813
00:58:19,530 --> 00:58:22,599
Here. Shall we eat it?

814
00:58:31,210 --> 00:58:34,280
Shall we add this? Let's add this.

815
00:58:34,880 --> 00:58:37,019
What's next? Let's see.

816
00:58:37,349 --> 00:58:39,820
Dad, my nose is bleeding.

817
00:58:40,559 --> 00:58:42,460
What is that? Are you okay?

818
00:58:42,460 --> 00:58:44,590
I fooled you!

819
00:58:46,230 --> 00:58:47,360
Eun Ha.

820
00:58:47,960 --> 00:58:49,260
Eun Ha?

821
00:58:50,230 --> 00:58:52,730
- Mom!
- My sweetie.

822
00:58:52,769 --> 00:58:53,940
You're home.

823
00:58:55,000 --> 00:58:57,010
Eun Ha, Mom is tired.

824
00:58:57,010 --> 00:58:59,039
No, I'm not.
I'm so happy right now.

825
00:58:59,539 --> 00:59:00,710
Come here, honey.

826
00:59:01,780 --> 00:59:02,909
Did you have a long day?

827
00:59:02,909 --> 00:59:04,949
Come on, give me some energy.

828
00:59:06,250 --> 00:59:08,119
Good work.

829
00:59:10,219 --> 00:59:12,190
Eun Ha, can you giggle like that
again?

830
00:59:12,190 --> 00:59:13,860
I love that sound.

831
00:59:14,090 --> 00:59:15,619
You need to make me laugh.

832
00:59:15,920 --> 00:59:18,889
- Shall I tickle you?
- Dad, help me.

833
00:59:18,989 --> 00:59:20,230
Shall I make Mom laugh too?

834
00:59:21,199 --> 00:59:22,559
Help me!

835
00:59:22,860 --> 00:59:24,269
Eun Ha, let's run away.

836
00:59:24,929 --> 00:59:27,039
I'm going to catch you.

837
00:59:27,070 --> 00:59:28,940
Come here!

838
00:59:29,699 --> 00:59:31,039
Let's run away!

839
00:59:32,539 --> 00:59:34,239
I caught you.

840
01:00:38,010 --> 01:00:42,110
(Where the Morning Star Hovers)

841
01:01:09,440 --> 01:01:13,909
(Flower of Evil)

842
01:01:17,079 --> 01:01:18,980
His thumbnail is missing again.

843
01:01:18,980 --> 01:01:20,980
It's exactly the same as
the Yeonju Serial Murder Case...

844
01:01:20,980 --> 01:01:22,320
that occurred in 2002.

845
01:01:24,119 --> 01:01:26,590
The case Reporter Kim mentioned
last time?

846
01:01:27,889 --> 01:01:29,789
If you're in too much pain,

847
01:01:31,090 --> 01:01:32,429
don't hold back and tell me.

848
01:01:33,260 --> 01:01:35,500
Then things will get
more interesting for me.

849
01:01:35,800 --> 01:01:36,800
Where is Mom?

850
01:01:36,829 --> 01:01:39,800
Mom said she's going to clean
your workroom.
